

/////// OVERVIEW: 
A one-shot GCS batch ingestion job for running the full PRS workflow in Google Cloud composed of 4 files:
index.js
package.json
dockerfile
cloud_sdk.mjs



/////// STEPS 1-10:
1. Create the prs-job folder
cd ~
mkdir -p prs-job
cd prs-job
2. Add index.js

Open the Cloud Shell editor:

cloudshell edit index.js

Paste the index.js code you uploaded. It imports fetchAllScores, getTxts, PGP functions, and Match2 from ./cloud_sdk.mjs, then runs the full workflow:

PGP users â†’ 23andMe files â†’ PGS models â†’ PRS results â†’ GCS

Your uploaded index.js saves outputs under:

prs_workflow/
  pgp/
  pgs/
  prs_results/
  manifests/
  errors/

and requires cloud_sdk.mjs in the same folder.

3. Add cloud_sdk.mjs

Copy the working cloud SDK from your polygenic_risk_scores build:

cp ~/polygenic_risk_scores/dist/cloud_sdk.mjs ~/prs-job/cloud_sdk.mjs

Test it:

node -e "import('./cloud_sdk.mjs').then(m => console.log(Object.keys(m))).catch(console.error)"

You should see exports like:

fetchAllScores
getTxts
fetchAvailableDataTypes
allUsersMetaDataByType_fast
fetchProfile
get23Txt
Match2
4. Create package.json
cat > package.json <<'EOF'
{
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node index.js"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@google-cloud/storage": "^7.16.0"
  }
}
EOF
5. Create Dockerfile
cat > Dockerfile <<'EOF'
FROM node:20

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install

COPY . .

CMD ["node", "index.js"]
EOF
6. Check the folder
ls

You should see:

Dockerfile
cloud_sdk.mjs
index.js
package.json
7. Build the container
gcloud builds submit --tag gcr.io/personalgenomes/prs-job
8. Deploy the Cloud Run Job
gcloud run jobs deploy prs-import \
  --image gcr.io/personalgenomes/prs-job \
  --region us-central1 \
  --memory 4Gi \
  --task-timeout 60m \
  --set-env-vars BUCKET_NAME=personalgenomes-23andme-data,USER_LIMIT=3,PGS_LIMIT=3,BATCH_SIZE=1
9. Run it
gcloud run jobs execute prs-import \
  --region us-central1
10. Check outputs
gcloud storage ls gs://personalgenomes-23andme-data/prs_workflow/
gcloud storage ls gs://personalgenomes-23andme-data/prs_workflow/prs_results/
gcloud storage ls gs://personalgenomes-23andme-data/prs_workflow/errors/

Keep USER_LIMIT=3 and PGS_LIMIT=3 for the first test. After it works, increase them gradually.



////////////////// SUMMARY:

What each file does
File	Purpose
index.js	Main workflow script. It fetches PGP 23andMe users, loads genotype files, fetches PGS Catalog scoring files, runs PRS matching with Match2, and saves outputs to Google Cloud Storage.
cloud_sdk.mjs	Node-safe SDK bundle used by index.js. It should export PGP, PGS, and PRS functions without browser-only code such as Plotly, LocalForage, window, or document.
package.json	Defines the Node.js project settings and dependencies, especially @google-cloud/storage.
Dockerfile	Builds the container image that Cloud Run executes.

Your uploaded index.js imports fetchAllScores, getTxts, fetchAvailableDataTypes, allUsersMetaDataByType_fast, fetchProfile, get23Txt, and Match2 from ./cloud_sdk.mjs. It also sets USER_LIMIT, PGS_LIMIT, and BATCH_SIZE from environment variables.

Workflow

The job runs this pipeline:

PGP public 23andMe metadata
  â†’ fetch participant profiles
  â†’ download/load 23andMe genotype files
  â†’ fetch PGS Catalog score metadata
  â†’ download/load selected PGS scoring files
  â†’ run PRS matching for every user Ã— PGS pair
  â†’ save results to Google Cloud Storage
