Key steps inside index.js

The script first checks the available PGP data types, then fetches all 23andMe participant metadata. It limits the number of users with USER_LIMIT, then loads each userâ€™s profile and genotype data in batches.

It then fetches all PGS Catalog score metadata, selects the first PGS_LIMIT scores, downloads their scoring files with getTxts, and saves both metadata and parsed score files to GCS.

Finally, it creates every user Ã— PGS pair and runs:

Match2(pgsObj.txt, userObj.genotype)

Each PRS result is saved under:

prs_workflow/prs_results/{userId}/{pgsId}.json

If a result already exists, the script skips it, which gives you basic checkpointing.
